Using the Java API documentation:
- On IntelliJ IDEA put the mouse crusor on a keyword and press "ctrl + q"
- Documentation is available on the web or can be downloaded locally.
  - Web - http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/
  - Download - http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/download/index.html
- To integrate the Java API documentation into the IntelliJ IDEA:
  - Go to IntelliJ Welcome Screen
  - Select Configure -> Project Defaults -> Project Structures
  - On the left side under "Platform Settings" select "SDKs"
  - Select "Documentation Paths" tab
  - Click on the '+' icon to specify the URL
  - Enter the documentation URL
  - Click "Ok"
- Now in the IntelliJ IDEA select a keyword and press "Shift + F1" to open the
  Java Documentation.
